==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/skrɪp/}}

===Etymology 1===
An apheticism of Old French ''[[escreppe]]'' ‘purse, alms-bag’, a varient of ''[[escherpe]]'' or of Old Norse ''[[skreppa]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# a small medieval [[bag]] used to carry food, money, utensils etc.
#:*'''1964''': A night promising fair, scented, the moon in her third quarter, nightingales in the wood, WS, in worn cloak against the morning’s chill, empty '''scrip''' and purse, taking the road. — Anthony Burgess, ''Nothing Like the Sun''

===Etymology 2===
{{wikipedia}}
Probably from a conflation of ''[[script]]'' and ''[[scrap]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# a [[scrap]] of [[paper]]
# a [[document]] certifying possession of [[land]], or in lieu of [[money]]

===Etymology 3===
Abbreviation of ''[[subscription]] [[receipt]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# a [[share]] [[certificate]]

===Etymology 4===
Abbreviation of ''[[prescription]]'' (informal, British).

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# a [[medical]] [[prescription]]

